    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Central Heating Installation Formby. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Formby homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does central heating installation cost in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A full central heating installation in Formby starts from £3,500 for a smaller single-zone property. Larger Formby properties with multi-zone systems typically fall between £5,500 and £8,000 depending on number of radiators, zones, underfloor circuits and whether a cylinder is included. All prices are confirmed at a written fixed-price site survey. No surprises on invoice day for any installation size.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">MULTI-ZONE</span>&nbsp; Can you install multi-zone heating in my Formby property?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Multi-zone heating with separate circuits for upstairs and downstairs, or for extension areas, is one of our most common Formby installations. We design zone systems at the free survey for properties with 10 or more radiators. Nest and Hive multi-zone smart controls are available as part of the system. A properly designed multi-zone system in a large Formby property reduces heating bills by 15 to 25% compared to a single-zone setup.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">UNDERFLOOR</span>&nbsp; Can you connect underfloor heating to my central heating system?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Wet underfloor heating circuits connected to the system boiler are common in our Formby extension and renovation installations. We design and install the underfloor circuit alongside the main radiator system. The underfloor circuit connects via a dedicated zone and manifold, with its own thermostat. This is the correct approach for a kitchen extension or open plan ground floor renovation in a Formby home.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">G3</span>&nbsp; Are you G3 qualified for unvented cylinder installation in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our engineers hold G3 qualification for unvented cylinder work. This is a legal requirement. We design, install and certify unvented cylinders as part of the full central heating installation for multi-bathroom Formby properties. The G3 annual inspection certificate can be issued on the same visit as the annual boiler service.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">HOW LONG</span>&nbsp; How long does a full central heating installation take in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A standard single-zone installation in a 3 to 4-bed Formby property takes 3 to 5 days. A multi-zone system in a larger property takes 5 to 7 days. A complex renovation project with underfloor circuits, multi-zone and cylinder takes 7 to 10 days. All timelines confirmed at the free survey and fixed in the written quote. We work to agreed completion dates.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Formby central heating installation?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All central heating installations in Formby are carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe and G3 qualified engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
